vocabulary.definition: to save someone from a dangerous or harmful situation
vocabulary.example: The firefighters rescued the cat from the burning building.

vocabulary.definition: to make someone calm or sleepy by giving them a drug
vocabulary.example: The dentist needed to sedate the patient before the procedure.

vocabulary.definition: not awake or aware of what is happening
vocabulary.example: After the accident, he remained unconscious for several hours.

vocabulary.definition: related to activities done for enjoyment or relaxation rather than as a job
vocabulary.example: He enjoys recreational activities like hiking and swimming.

vocabulary.definition: showing no signs of stopping or lessening in intensity; persistently harsh or inflexible
vocabulary.example: The detective had a relentless drive to solve the case.

vocabulary.definition: a skeptical attitude; doubt as to the truth of something
vocabulary.example: There was skepticism among the team regarding the new strategy.
